### Cooldown Description

The cooldown is a mechanism that prevents an action from being performed too frequently. It's commonly used in games, APIs, and other systems where rate limiting is necessary.

### Cooldown Properties

| Property | Description | Type | Default |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| duration | The amount of time the cooldown lasts | number | 10 |
| resetOnAction | Whether the cooldown resets when the action is performed | boolean | true |

### Cooldown Usage

```javascript
class Cooldown {
  constructor(duration, resetOnAction = true) {
    this.duration = duration;
    this.resetOnAction = resetOnAction;
    this.lastActionTime = 0;
  }

  isOnCooldown() {
    const currentTime = Date.now();
    return currentTime - this.lastActionTime < this.duration;
  }

  resetCooldown() {
    if (this.resetOnAction) {
      this.lastActionTime = Date.now();
    }
  }
}

